With further investigation it is apparent that this bug is JDK specific and not a TPTP problem.  
This bug is reproducible using eclipse-SDK-3.2.1-win32 without any other plug-in?s.  
To reproduce this bug:
1. Install eclipse
2. Install java 1.4.2 runtime
3. File > New > Plug-in project
4. Specify Plug-in name
5. Click next twice to get to Templates page
6. Select "Plug-in with a multi-page editor"
7. Click: Next, Next, Finish
8. Run > Run..> Eclipse Application
9. Under Runtime_JRE: specify java 1.4.2
10. Click Run

11. Once the new workbench is launched, create a General Project
12. Create a file called MyFile.mpe under the new general project 
13. Open MyFile.mpe , and you will see the error specified in this bug


If you go back to step 9, and specify java 1.5.0 and you will not see this bug.

Valentina could you re-assign this bug to the correct eclipse component.  
Thank You
